<item>
            <title>[SPARK-5801] Shuffle creates too many nested directories</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-5801</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running Spark on EC2, there are 4 nested shuffle directories before the hashed directory names, for example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/mnt/spark/spark-5824d912-25af-4187-bc6a-29ae42cd78e5/spark-675133f0-b2c8-44a1-8775-5e394674609b/spark-69c1ea15-4e7f-454a-9f57-19763c7bdd17/spark-b036335c-60fa-48ab-a346-f1b420af2027/0c&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My understanding is that this should look like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/mnt/spark/spark-5824d912-25af-4187-bc6a-29ae42cd78e5/0c&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happened when I was using the sort-based shuffle (all default configurations for Spark on EC2).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is not a correctness problem (the shuffle still works fine).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
